dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling b Gulbadin Naib 51 (60b 4x4 2x6 104m) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: Cleans 'em up. Naib sends the middle stump cartwheeling. Fairly straight ball, Stirling plays all around this. He looks to open the bat-face and probably run it fine. Naib makes the shot look even worse. Most batsmen would have looked to drive that through cover or down the ground

dismissalComment.html: Rashid provides Afghanistan with the breakthrough! The off stump is knocked back. This is the legbreak from Rashid. Spins back into the left-hander and dips. Rashid storms through the gate and hits off and middle. Rashid, playing his 26th ODI, takes his 50th wicket. He is among the fastest to the landmark

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie c Shafiqullah b Rashid Khan 7 (9b 1x4 0x6 15m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: looks to slog across the line, manages a top-edge that was swirling in the air for a long, long time. Shafiqullah came running in a long way from deep square, but still wasn't certain to get a hand on it. Almost as an afterthought, he flung himself, diving full length forward as the ball lodged in his bucket hands. Rashid sprints to his mate to give him a high five. Spectacular catch that!

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson b Dawlat Zadran 5 (14b 0x4 0x6 21m) SR: 35.71

dismissalComment.html: sensational yorker. Pure pace. Class from Zadran. Full and furiously fast on middle, by the time the bat came down, the middle stump had been flattened. Used the crease well. Went wide and then got this to reverse back in a long way. Top-class. Waqar would've been proud of that delivery. Magical

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! That is special. The pressure of dot balls got to Tarakai. Murtagh, like he has been doing, takes pace off the ball with an offcutter. Tarakai goes through with a lofted drive but gets more elevation than distance. It hags in the air for a while. The fielder at long-on scurries across to his right, keeps his eyes on the ball all along and takes a lovely catch at deep midwicket. It doesn't have the aesthetics of a one-handed screamer but that is a brilliant take. Needed so many things to go right, did 'em all.

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c Thompson b Dockrell 39 (50b 3x4 2x6 54m) SR: 78

dismissalComment.html: done in this time! Stanikzai goes. Against the ball turning away, that's a dangerous option because if it does spin, then it opens you up to this. Stanikzai wanted to hit that over long-on again but takes the outside half and skews down to long-off. The previous six was also fraught with risk, but that one didn't turn and he got closer to the pitch. This one, he was done in by good bowling. The length was shorter

headshotImage.longCaption: Rahmat Shah player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Shah seals the series with a six! He hares down the track, takes it on the half-volley, and blasts it over the bowler's head

commentPostTextItems.html: 4.50pm Afghanistan follow up the T20 series win with the ODI series win. This seven-wicket victory caps a dominant few weeks for Stanikzai's men. They bask in glory and celebrate. Rashid Khan, who set it up for his team with four wickets, animatedly pumps his fist.

Afghanistan were chasing for the first time this series. They lost Shahzad and Tarakai, the debutant, early but Shah and Stanikzai put Afghanistan back on track with a 73-run stand. Stanikzai fell for 39, but Shah moved to his second ODI hundred and provided the coup de grce with a six. Shenwari also prospered, marking his return with an unbeaten fifty. Do stick around for the presentation
Fawad Saleh: "Rahmat, Nabi, Rashid, Sami, Dawlat will go onto become good Test players as well."
Harsh Dubey: "What a way to finish the match, Shah does a Dhoni."
Harsh Dubey: "Well deserved hundred by Rahmat, he deserves the Man of the Match award too."
Anmol lakhmani: "A very very high-quality knock from rahmat shah! A lad with great future ahead .."
Rahmat Shah is the Man of the Match
Shah: We just took our time on this wicket. It was nice to bat on and win it. We have put in a lot of hard work for the last two-three months.
Paul Stirling is the Man of the Series

Stirling: It was nice to get a few runs and contribute. Today we were outplayed, Rahmat took the game away from us. Afghanistan deserved the win. I like playing in the subcontinent. The ball does not do much and we can play some expansive shots. The Intercontinental Cup is a massive game for us. Hopefully we learn from these games and go well.

<Rashid Khan, needless to say, is the best bowler of the series: I am really happy. The way te captain supported me, he gave me motivation. I just gave my 100%. Most of the wickets in Asia suit the spinners and I will do my best in the IPL as well.
Stirling is the best batsman of the series

Porterfield, Ireland captain: I think we were 20-30 light with the bat. 250-260 would have made an interesting chase. Rahmat played well and took them over the line. As Paul mentioned, the last few months have done a world of good. Congratulations to Afghanistan. I am pleased with how we fought till the end.

Stanikzai, Afghanistan captain: Last few months we have won two T20 and two ODI series. Dawlat Zadran bowling well is a good sign for us. Today Shah and Shenwari played very well and showed their ability and experience.

Stanikzai collects the trophy and rejoices with his team-mates. That is all we have for you from this match. Thanks for reading. Looking forward to your company  for the Intercontinental Cup four-day match, which starts on March 28. Until then, goodbye.

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce b Rashid Khan 42 (52b 6x4 1x6 67m) SR: 80.76

dismissalComment.html: Rashid provides Afghanistan with the breakthrough! The off stump is knocked back. This is the legbreak from Rashid. Spins back into the left-hander and dips. Rashid storms through the gate and hits off and middle. Rashid, playing his 26th ODI, takes his 50th wicket. He is among the fastest to the landmark

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling b Gulbadin Naib 51 (60b 4x4 2x6 104m) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: Cleans 'em up. Naib sends the middle stump cartwheeling. Fairly straight ball, Stirling plays all around this. He looks to open the bat-face and probably run it fine. Naib makes the shot look even worse. Most batsmen would have looked to drive that through cover or down the ground

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield c Mohammad Shahzad b Fareed Ahmad 34 (52b 4x4 0x6 69m) SR: 65.38

dismissalComment.html: edged and taken. Good length and outside off, Porterfield is stapled to the crease as he drives loosely and nicks it to the left of Shahzad. Simple, waist-high catch

headshotImage.caption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rashid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie c Shafiqullah b Rashid Khan 7 (9b 1x4 0x6 15m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: looks to slog across the line, manages a top-edge that was swirling in the air for a long, long time. Shafiqullah came running in a long way from deep square, but still wasn't certain to get a hand on it. Almost as an afterthought, he flung himself, diving full length forward as the ball lodged in his bucket hands. Rashid sprints to his mate to give him a high five. Spectacular catch that!

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson b Dawlat Zadran 5 (14b 0x4 0x6 21m) SR: 35.71

dismissalComment.html: sensational yorker. Pure pace. Class from Zadran. Full and furiously fast on middle, by the time the bat came down, the middle stump had been flattened. Used the crease well. Went wide and then got this to reverse back in a long way. Top-class. Waqar would've been proud of that delivery. Magical

dismissalText.commentary: Niall O'Brien lbw b Rashid Khan 34 (52b 3x4 0x6 77m) SR: 65.38

dismissalComment.html: plumb this time. Once again the doubt was created because Rashid was getting the ball to spun both ways. This time he played for the wrong'un only to see the ball cut back in and hit him plumb in front of middle. Made the mistake of tucking the bat behind the pad as well. Ireland in big trouble. 280 was on the cards not too long ago. That could be whittled down to 230 or so at this rate. Inspired bowling change from Stanikzai

dismissalComment.html: slices the full delivery to third man. The catch is as easy as they come. Sashayed down the pitch to smoke that over cover but the bat face turned in his hand as he made contact. Intent right, execution wrong. Point fielder did well to heed to his mate's call

dismissalText.commentary: George Dockrell b Fareed Ahmad 21 (21b 2x4 0x6 28m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: the middle stump is flattened. Length ball angling in from wide of the crease, he backed away to go over cover but missed it altogether because he swung through too early. Ireland, who looked good for 280, now in danger of not lasting their full quota

dismissalComment.html: bangs a short ball on middle, he goes across a long way to help it along to fine leg but the ball got big on him and he ended up gloving it to the keeper. As simple as they come for him.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Shahzad c Porterfield b Thompson 13 (19b 1x4 1x6 19m) SR: 68.42

dismissalComment.html: sensational catch! Looked to smash that over cover but didn't get to the pitch of the ball and ended up slicing it to point where Porterfield threw himself to his left and caught that with both hands. The danger man is gone

headshotImage.caption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Barry McCarthy player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Najeeb Tarakai c sub (BJ McCarthy) b Murtagh 5 (18b 0x4 0x6 33m) SR: 27.77

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! That is special. The pressure of dot balls got to Tarakai. Murtagh, like he has been doing, takes pace off the ball with an offcutter. Tarakai goes through with a lofted drive but gets more elevation than distance. It hags in the air for a while. The fielder at long-on scurries across to his right, keeps his eyes on the ball all along and takes a lovely catch at deep midwicket. It doesn't have the aesthetics of a one-handed screamer but that is a brilliant take. Needed so many things to go right, did 'em all.

headshotImage.caption: Rahmat Shah player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rahmat Shah player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Rahmat Shah not out 108 (128b 10x4 1x6 164m) SR: 84.37
Asghar Afghan c Thompson b Dockrell 39 (50b 3x4 2x6 54m) SR: 78

dismissalComment.html: done in this time! Stanikzai goes. Against the ball turning away, that's a dangerous option because if it does spin, then it opens you up to this. Stanikzai wanted to hit that over long-on again but takes the outside half and skews down to long-off. The previous six was also fraught with risk, but that one didn't turn and he got closer to the pitch. This one, he was done in by good bowling. The length was shorter
